        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 6:34PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 634 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Maxie, or 11 miles northeast of Wiggins, moving east at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Perry
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
